#ELLEBeauty: Perfume is often called the invisible accessory, but it honestly works more like a mood diary you wear on your skin. Some days call for something bright and energising, other days need something soft and comforting. Over time, those small decisions start to tell a story, capturing moods, memories, and phases of life in a way that feels surprisingly personal. Head to the 🔗 in bio to discover your perfect scent of the day.
